text: Rose daughter of walter Ball of Dublin alderman and maior, and wife to Luke Challoner doctoure of Divinity by whom shee had issue divers children (all deade younge one daughter excepted named Phoebe) deceased of the plague the sixe and twentieth of October ano 1604. and is bur- in Trinitie colledge by Dublin with moste of her issue.
Mary daughter of James Rian sometime d'lireve of Dublin and wife to Richard noble gentleman, deceased at Thri- stledermotte in December the yeere of grace 1604. and is bur.: in Dublin.

Mary Lady Tyrell, dr. of Walter segrave alderman maio[r] of Dublin, & wi[fe] to Sir John Tyrell Knight ald: and maior of the same cittie: deceased in December 1604. and is, bur[ied in St. Audoens, churche. Shee had issue walter, Mathew Richarde, Edward, Cicilie (wife to Nichas Stevens, some time shireve of Dublin) Marg. and three more deade in theire infaucie.

Martin Zlake of Athboy, learned in the lawes, was bur[ied] in the church of Athboy the thirde of March 1604 He had to wife Erzabeth daughter of Michael Fitz- Fitz-williams of Donamor, second sonne of Richard of- Merion.
Peter Bolton provoste marshall of Leinster deceased the fourth of March 1604. of a wounde which some dayes be- fore he receaved in the streetes of Dublin.

Adam Loftum 20: Archb[ishop] of Dublin & Lo[rd] Chauncelour and thrice Lo[rd] Justice of Irelande had to wife jane da of James Pourdon gent. by whome he had issue Sir Dudley Lof[tus[  Sr Edward Lo[ftus] Capt. Adam Lo[ftus]  Sr Thomas Loftus knight and Henry Loftus, besides many other sonnees- dead younge: Margt. wife to Sir George Colley Knight, Isabel

Esabell to Sr. William vnther Knight, Also to Sr Henry werren Knight, Martha to Sr. Thoms Colclough Knight Anne firste to cap. Henry Colley, 2. to Capn. George Blounte, and 3. to St. Edward Blanep Knight, Jane Sr. Francis Berkley Knight, and Dorothie to St. John More Knight. The Lo: Chauncelour deceased at St. Sepuschero the fiste of Aprill 1605. the 72. yeere of his age, the 24 yeere of his Chauncelourship and of hio sonsecracon, and is buried in St. Paterickeo Dublin.

Winifrid, dr of Antonio Toto a Florentin, of K. H. vm. privie chamber and hic Serieant pannter) and wite: to St. Charlea, Calthorpe Knight (sometime Attorney) generall and now one of the zusticee of the common pleach deceased the firste of Auguste 1605. She leste noe issue by S. Charles

William Fitz williamor of Jobston deceased of the pleasure at: Merion the xxiij. of Aug: 1605: he did a few weekes before many Bonnet dr. of Eerald Pirne of Ballyhorsee and had no issue, he io bur: in the church of Talaugh

S. George Bourchier Knight master of the Ordinannc and of the privie Councell of Ireland, z. sonne to Jo: Erle Bath, had to wite Martha sister of Charles, howar (E of Noting: etc. by whome He leste istue Thomas John and Henry, He deceased the xxiiii. Septemb: 1605. and ioj bur- in Christchurch Dublin. Also verfol 42
sameer ^Taysour shireve of Dublin deceased the twentieth of December 1605.

John Barnewall of Brimore had to wi: Fleonor dr of Sr. James Dowdall k. chiefe just: of y kinges, bencis by whome- He had ihre jamees, Richard, K dward, Peter, Paterick, Ro¬ bart & Andrew: Margt. wi: to Edw: Taase of Gookeston. Mary to La-Pleminge of derpatrick, Elizab: to Rich: Wernon of Staba: nan, Ima, Alleen, Kathern, Anne, Brigid, ursula, & Eleonor. He deceased at Brimore etc. xii. of Febr: 1605. & is. bur: at Balrothrie.

Marcus Barnewall of Dromnagh mar: de: of prarc Barnewall of Donbroe by whome he had inue only Elizab wise to James Barnewall of Brymore, he deceased af Ty¬ rinoute y x. g'Lune 1606. and is bur: in his owne chap: pell by Dromnagh. he was a man of ordinary statue but Geytraordinary strength. Any his wi: deceased about the xiiij. eoctob: following and is, bur: in Balrodrie

James Bellieu of Dublin alderm: maior had to wi: Cleonor Dr. of Michaell Penteney ald: ma: by whom he lette istte only Elizas: wife to Thomas white of Dublin merchant now dwellinge at the ward. He deceased viii. Aug: 1606.
Thomas Iillon chiefe Iustice of connagh deceased the xxviijte. of Septemb: 1606. 20 but in Dublin. Hier wife was Elice sister to Sr. Fraunceo, staen Knight,
Arthure Chichester sonne to St. Arthure chichester Knight Co: Dey: etc. wag Borne ye xxxth of September 1606. and deceased the xxxv s of October neyte followinge and ien bur: in Christchurch.

Christofer Pussell of Seaton mar: Elizab: dr. of william Talbot of Malahide, by whom he had issue Bartholmew Katherin & Atary. He deceased the xvth of Decemb: 1606 and is bur: in the church of Swerdess,

Adrian Slabaerte sometime of Bruges in fflandere merchant, had to wife jane dr of Blance of Bruge goldsmith by whom he had issue Reginalde, who died in schisbonne with his wife and all hio children, Rennginen dead aged yom. y: Hester e josian virginge livinge in London with theire mother. He deceased the iiij. of Jhebr 1606. aged about lxxvj. peeresz. isz bur: in Tallagh.
Thornton, Fallofeild wife of cap. George ^ and after of Basset some time of wicombe in Cornewall deceased very aged the firste of March 1605. and lette noe issue.
Fraunceobaughte of John Harpeny clerke of the munition z wife to Phiuppe conran alderman maior of Dublin, de- ceased ψ ψπι. Ayrill 1606.

Joan dr. of George Lodge, had to her firste husband Rate Grimedich, farmer of the customes of y porte of Dublin fathe by her to Richard, Henry, George, Thomas & Charles: alsoe to 2/tary (wise of George Loe clerte in the comon pleae) Hester & Martha. Shee had to her seconde husband Edward — Smith pencioner by whom shee had noe issue. Shee diei the xxv. of Aprill 1607. rol bur: in Christchurch.

Sir Nicholas Saint Laurence Knight Lorde Bay of'Houth had to his firste wise Margaret daught of Sir Christofer Barnewall of Turvie lmght by whom he had issue Sir Christofer Samt Laurence Knight now Lorde of houth, Thomao, and Marywise to william (Eustace of Castlemartin. Hio second wise was Mary dt. of Sir Aico: White inight mr. of the soleo, by whom He had issue Edward Rich.
Richard, Amory, Margaret wife to Jemco vicount of God manston, Eleonor and Alles. He was buried at Houth by one and twentieth of May one thousand sixe hundte sand seven.

Nicolaojseldest sonre of Dridley second sonne of Sir Ni colae, Bageriall Knight, marshall of Ireland, had to wife, Anne de. of Sir Thomas Cosclough of Tinterne knight, by whom he had only issue Mary. He was wounded in¬ light by william Sentleger in Dublin the xvij. of Iune 1607. whereof he died xix. and io vur: in Christchurck

John Ifinglaen of was, beston was buried at was pleston the eight and twentieth of June 1607. he had three wiveg, etc. 2 was Elisab: Dr. of Sir Christofer Barnewall of Turvie, by who he leste issue, Richard, Christofer, Margaret, Aseen, Jane, Kate¬ rin, Mary, gennet & Fraunces. Hio second wife was Mar¬ garet dr. of Patericke sonne of Thomo Kinglas, sonne to the schiefe Baron, & widow to Andrew white of Leipsip, by whom he leste noe issue. hio thirde wije was Cicilie dr. of Henry Cu¬ sake of Dub: ia: Dowager of houth, by whom likewise he lefte noe istire.

V. Nicolas, younge, (ldest sonne to Gerald younge of Dublin- alderman maior deceased xxvo. Aug: 1607. He had to wife Agneo daughter of James Rian sometimes Shireve of Dub: by whom he had isue hio oue childe zameo.

Mary dr. of Sir Nicholas White k. mr. of the Roseg and second wife to Robart Browne of Molranan (all whose children by (her died younge) was after second wife to Cristofer Darcy of platten, by whom shee had islice Nicholaer Christofer: (hee was thirdly second wise to Sir Nichaes Lo: of houth by whome shee had isue as before fol: 6. Thee deceased p 25. of July 1607.10 Bur at Houth.

Richard Netervise of Corballico seconde sonne Luke Netervise of douth deceased the sitie of sey temb: 1607. and 10 but; in the church of Donapate, He had to wife Alles etc. of Sir Jo: Pluncket of Donsaghly k. chiefe zustice of the Kingees, bench by whom he had noe issue, and theresore made Nichae, Netervise of Douth hio, nephew- Thion adopted heire
Mseo dr. of Thomao Tisher, aged above threescore yeereos: deceased ye 23. of Novemb. 1607. Shee lived vnmartied and died a maide, loj bur: in Christchurch.

John Arthure alderman maior of Dublin had to wife Alee dr. of Hugh Kenedie of D. march: by whome he had ijsne Edward, George, Robte, Thomas and William: Iitzabetz Cleonor, and two daughtero more. He decea sed y xj. of Decemb: 1607.10 bur: in Saint Patrick, Dublin in the parish church

Sr. Henry Gronkar Knighte Lorde President of Moun ster, deceased the 3rd. of June 1607. and is bur: in St. Ma ries in Corke: he had to wife Anne dr. of Parker¬ Ho: Morley, by whome he had issue william, Edwarde, Henry: Katherin, Elizabeth and Fraunceor.
Lo: Cromwell deceased the vynnth. of Septemb: 2IIe, de vii.

Marion dr. and heire of Laurence Sherle of Shallon in the countie of Meath, deceased the vjte. of Januarie 1607. Her husbandes, and issue appeare in the visitacon boore of the countie of Dublin. fo 3 b

William voldinge of Dublin merchant deceased xvjth of I febr: 1607. and io bur: in Christ-church. he had to: wife Margerie dr. of m. Broune sometime fhirife of Dub: by whome he had issue Richard, Nicolas and Elizabeth aff younge children.

John Sanckie of Dublin deceased the xym, of ffebruary 1607 ⁊ io bur: in St. Johno churche. Te had to wi: Anne d? ot Thomason sometime threr of St. Patrickes Dublin, by whome he sefte istue Richard, Namlet and Margaret all younge.

Eleonor wi: to Robte Rochforde of Kilbride & dr of Sr. Lucae dillon kn: ch: B of y exch: deceased the xxvjtt of febr: 1607. a 10 vnrs: in Newton. Shee had issue: John, Chropher, Lule, Thomas Barnabie, & Robarte: Marg. wi: to Patricke hussy B. of Gastrum, Jane to¬ walter Dongan of Pauciston get. f Brigid vnmar.

I Siver pluncket Baron of Louth deceased the sitte day o 2) tarch 1607. & 10 bur: at Tallanston. He hadte hie firste Frauncis dr. of St. Nicolas Gagenall Knight, mar¬ wife shall of y army. by whome he had isue Mathew now ro: of Louth & Sywester: Margt. wife to Sr. Thomo Fitz- williams of Merion t. Mary to Henry sonne & to Sr Jo. Draycotte k. Iinay, Anne & Clenor. hic second wi: was Bennet Doudall widow of Bath sometime seconde Iustice in the common pleas by whome the Baron had no illi

Mary Gray deceased the ixth of March 1607. & is but: in St. Batherins by Thomascourt. Shee had to her first husband John Gennynge to her second willm pagotte and to her thirde Gilles Allen both Commetime Majors of Dublin & without issue by her. Jo: Grunyngs was of the house of Hungerforde in Bartshire by whom shee lefte issue John, who hath vifr Anne dr. of one bigot in wales by the sister of Wm. pag: aforesaide; des Sterben had to wife Margt. Dr. of Gilb: pourdon as in fol: 20. of the first funriall hooke: Mary, who had to her first husb: one Brunet, to heir. lleid, to her 3. Walter Edney now shirrbe of the county of Dublin: Joan, who had to her hush: Jo: Marshall as in fol: 1o. of the hooke now citid, to her 2. Jo: Broune dometime clerke of the checque, and now to her 3. Edward Barry gent.

Joan harte widow of Robart Legge gent. deceased the xii. of Marche M.D.C.vii. and io but in St. Michaelo in Dub. dheelefte ihre Pentecost wise to Richard Hoper sometimes deputie vice-threr. and Elisab: wi: to James Carroll cham¬ bersam of the exchecque & deputie threr. at warres.

Mary dr. of Sr. Nicho St. Laurence Kn. Baron of South & wi: of wch. Gustace of Castlemartin deceased secundo A Ror. M. DC. vrij. and to bur: in y church of yt toune. Shee lefte istue Maurrice etc. Godfrey, Mary & Elizabeth.

Robart Aß of the Naas etc. etc. deceased etc. Aprilis Nr. de vn. he had to wife Elizab: dre. of James Flatesbury of lhonston by whom he had issue Thomas, Walter, James wittm, Henry-Mathew. Margt. wi: to hameo wellichsey Katherin etc.

Also dt. of waster Segraue of Dublin Alderman Maior & wi: of John eldest sonne of Richard Pagan Ald: n2. of sy samie, deceased the xym. of may grs. DE. viiq. & is but: in St. Andoeno, church. Shee was mother to Richard, Thomas, George & John: cicilie, Mary & Anne.
Cicilie holmes wife of Richard Fagan abonesaid deceas: o. Maii m. De. vii. a iosbur: in St. Andoeno. Shee¬ had istire John abouesaid & many. see fol of this Book 22,

Margt. dr. of Walter hop of Molingar deceased vstimo Maij ano. M. De. viii. shee was firste wite to Edward Tuite of Tuitston in com: Westmid: by whom shee had issue Edmund, wissiam and James: jane wife to Fraunces, (Edgeworth clerke of the Hanaper and Anne, wittj 2. more dead poinge. Ehee wach 2. wife to Michaell Chamberlin Alderman Mayor of Dub: by whome shee lefte issue, Edward, James and Christi beside many dead in theire infaucie.
Katherin de of Chropher Darcy of Platten and wise to william Mackwy of Ballineskeagh deceased m travaise of her firste childe (together with the 2 hisdt) the xii. of July 1608.
Mary do. and only childe of of Sr. John Talbot of Castfering Knight deceased younge and unmarried the x. of jusy 1608.

Angell Gueste sister to St. Lignell Gueste Knighte & wite to St. Henrie Croftee, Knighte (seconde brother of the house of Savon in Susfolke) deceased the yyvj. of July 1608. and is bur: in St. Johns in Dublin: hee leste issue by Sr. Henry Susan, Bged 2. y: her Theatley by whome firste husband was Ihee had ijsue Thomaez & Isabel.
John Jennynges of whome above in fol: 10. decea- sed 26. July 1608. and is, bur: in St. Patrickes Dublin: he leste ijsue Henty zennynges
Doctoure Roger God Lo: Byshoppe of theath and of the vrivie Councill deceased at Arbrackan the xxvij. of July 1608.

Sr. Richard Shee of Kilkeny Kinghte deceased the yth. of August 1608. He had to his first wife Margaret dr. of John Sherlocke of Waterforde by whome he had issue Robt. drad in England wout issue, Luke who hath to wi: Ellen dr. of V Edmand Butler Vicount of Mountgerrot, Thomas John and Marke: Letice wife to John Grace of Grace story, Ratherin to Edmund Cantwell of Murcarke, Margar. to James Walsh of Waterford and IJabel wife to David eldest sonne of Robte Rooth of Kilkeny. Sr. Richardes second wife (and widow now libinge) is margaret dr. of Christofer Fagan of Dublin alderman Mayor, by whom he lefte noe issue.

Iane Birford deceased the xv. Auguste 1608. Shee was wife of the Talbot of Cromlyn by whome shee had ihre william, Mathew, Adam ½ Robarte: (2) Elizabeth wije to Aicolas dillon: shee is buried in Cromsyn.

Capt. Odmund Leigh comaunder of the Omy in com: Tyrone deceased the iy. of Septemb: 1608. is bùr in Christchurch Dublin: he had to wije Elizabeth eldest dr. of Sr. George Parolet t. governour of the Derry by whome he had noe inue.
John targe, born in Picardie deceased the vvth. of September 1608.

Anne dr. of Rich: a/kereditl. sometimes to: Bi: of Legh sin & wi: to wm. eldest sonne of Sr. &c. Colley of Edendery Knight, deceased in childe-bedde of her first childe prm. Septemb: 1608. es, bur: in Patrictes Dubin in her father's tombe: the child (named william) alsoe died.

Sr. & Wray Fenton Knight principall secretary to the State, deceased 19: Octob: 1608. 2 10, bur: m. 5. Patrickes Dublin in westous tombe. he had to wife Alles (dr of the said Doctour weston sometimes 20: Chauncelour of Irland) by whome he leste ijue william feu¬ ton, & tatberin wife to Sr. Pichard Boise Knight.
Leonard St. Laurence thirde sonne of St. Christofer St. Laurence Knight 20: of houth deceased aboute the seventh of Novemb: 1608.

Alee, dr of Adam Loftus sometimes Lo: Chaunceloue of Ireland deceased the yu. of Novemb: 1608. Shee was wife to Sr. Henry warren of warrenston (or Ballybritten) in vfaly Knight, by whome shee never had issue, and io bur: in Ballemacwilliam.

Bartholmew Barnewall second Sonne of the house of Brimore deceased the firste of Januarie 1608. and is burt in Balradrie. He had to wi: Anne dr. of Robarte Bysse of Dublin, by whom the leste is sire James and Mary.

Margaret dr. of Richard Steredith Jometinne By- Ihoppe of Leghim, & wife of Christofer traway of Rathminee deceased in childbed of her firste childe the vii. of jan: 1608. & 10 bur: in St. patrickes Dublin in her fathere tombe: shee lefte ijsue a danghter

John Shefton of Dublin Alderman myor decea sed the 23. of March 1608. and sette illue by his firste wife (Wse dr. of Robte vijher of Santriffe) Thomas Sheston, and by his second wi: (Mary dr of Mathew handcocke alderman major of Dublin) Christofer Shefton a younge childe.

Dame Mary Barnewall wife of Sr. Patricke Barnewall of Gracesieu Knighte and dr of Sr. Nicolas Bagenall kinght, Cometime Marshall of the armie in Irelande, deceased the xi. of Aprill 1609 & is buried in Luske. Her issue appeareth at large in the Visitation boote of the countie of Dublin.

henry disson Attorny of the Province of ulter, & second sonne of Sr. Lucao dillon Knight sometime Cometime cheife Baron of the Exchequer in Ireland deceased the xviii. of Aprill 1609. He had to wife Elizabeth Culvever,

Pose dr. of James Boodman of Laghnanston & wife of John walsh late of the Shangenagh deceased the xxvjth of July 1609. and ien bur: in Rath michael. Shee had iisue Walter, Symon, James and Edmunde; Joan wife to Geralde Fitz-geralde of Allon, Margerie to John Delahide of Belantrie, Margaret to Henry eldeste Sonne of Theobalde walth of Killencarge, and Marion unmarried,
Iane dr. of Christofer Darcie of Platten & wife of walter Birte of Tullocke, deceased the viiijte. of Auguste 1609. Shee had ijsue Richarde, George, Christofer and Ra= therm.

James wolverston of Stallorgan had to wife Margare. dr. of Richarde Archpole of Kilmacud, and begate Ro: barte william Robarte, Christofer and John and a dr. that died younge. He deceased the yth of Sep: tember 1609. io bur: at Stallorgan.

Richard Woble deceased on Michaon day 1609. He had to. Thio firste wife Anne dr. of Captaine Jo: Barington by whome he had issue a sonne that deceased poringe etwo dto Anne wife to George Sonne of Sr. George Greame knight & Elizabeth. Hio second wife was was Mary dr. of Ja: Rian (as in fol: 1o.) by whome he lefte issue Alles.

Christofer Netervile of Blackcastle deceased the xxvjth of Betober 1609. His firste wije was Alles do. of Nichas brother to Sr. Jo: Tyrell Knight, on whome he begate Richard, Christian, Begnet, Elizabeth & Joan, His¬ second wife was Mary sister of ho: Barnewall of 2, Brymore, by whome he lud noe issue.

Martha wife of Sr. Thomas Colclough of Tinterne knighte deceased the of 1609. Shee had issue Thomas, whoe deceased a litle before her, Adam Pohn sberte & Richarde; Anne, Jane, Martha, Elenor¬ and Mary.

Philippe wife of Roger Dounton clerke of the pipe. ½ dt. of St. Edmunde Pelham Knighte sometime Griefe Baron of the Exchequer in Ireland and firste y had y titte of Lo: cheife Baron chere) deceased 1 orvf. of November 1609. wit hout sifferre.
Laurence white of Dublin merchante deceased the xxv. of December 1609. his matcheg and issue appeare in the visitacon booke of Dublin begonne m an. 1607.
Edward eldeste sonne of Richard Rounsell alderma mayor of Dublin deceased the seconde of Januarie 1609.

Sr. Ambrose forth Knight doctoure of the civill law and one of the mastere of the Chauncerie, deceased the xiij. of Januarie 1609. he had to his second wise Anne dr. of Edwarde Cusake of Lesmollin Sonne of Sr. Thomas, by whome he lefte isiue Robert Edward; Margaret and Elizabeth. He is buried in Christ-church Dublin.
George, tischer sometimes merchant of Dublin dec. the xixth of Januarie 1609. he had to wife Anne kenan and had issue Gerald that died before him Pose, cicelie, Katerin, Mary, Alecen etc. Jane.
Sr. Fraunces Stafford Knight
Cetervile and wife of Taafe deceased the xxvjth. of Januarie 1609.
Finglag and wife to Trissell of¬ Ruth deceased the fiste of Februarie 1609.
Nicolas Perdiffe Serieant at Law to his 2/ta. deceased the siste of Februarie 1609. he had to wise Margt. dr. of James Barry of Dublin
Nicolas Ball of Dublin alderman deceased the xxvjth of Februarie 1609. his wife and issue are entred in the visitacon booke of Dublin begonne in an. 1607. sur V.M.
Sir Ferdinando Freckleton Knight deceased the xxvij. Porter but of Februarie 1609. he had to wife leste noe ijsue.
Isabell daughter of Daniell Molyneux Ulster de = ceased porrige the zy. of March &c &cix
Jane dr. of Rob: Gisse of Dublin and wife to Sebastian fleminge of Drogheda deceased the xvii th of March 1609. & Peste ijue Mar¬ garet, Anne r Mary.

Mary Babington Lady dowager to Christofer late Lo: Baron of Dunsany was murthered at Clonny by Honora ny Caffery (nurse to one of her children) the xiyth of March 1609. Shee seste issue patricte now Lo: Baron of Dursany aged avoute fiftene yeeree & adaughter. Y knave not longe after executed for an other crime, cleered thio, wretched woman (who had suffered beinge burnte) & tooke the murther uppo Himselfe.

Elenor dr. of Richard Fitz-Symon of Balmadraughlyte dec: xxj. Martij 1609. Shee was wife sirste to wm. Bertrie of Dublin merchante, by whome hee had inue Joan & Anne wife to Laurence Duffe of Dublin. Esenor was secondly wife to Christofer fitz-willi- amor of Dublin merchant, by whome shee had noe sijsire.
Richard Holywood of Dublin deceased the xxiijth. of March 1609. he had to wife Anne Tipper mo¬ ther by him to Edward, Thomas, Rose, Elizabeth, and Mary
Richard Fagan of Dublin Alderman deceased the xxv. of March 1610. his wife isne appeare in the visitacon booke of Dublin: alsoe see fol: xj. of thien booke.

11 or 13 Elleg pluncket deceased the of Aprill 1610. Shee was wife of walter Hussie of Moise - hussie and was mother by him to Thomas, John, -- Nand etc. Saugh-Mathew, Meyser, Nicolaen; taterm, rose, Edt. Toy. To Boca Clenor, Elizabeth & Margaret. Elizabeth a for my mou
John only childe of Nicolaer Beydon of Irishton deceased before his father the xiiijth of Aprill 1610

Christofer Crus of the Naall deceased the xixth of Aprill 1610. His firste wise was Isabell dr. of Tho¬ mae Lutterell of Dublin, mother to Edward, Alex- ander; Mande & larion. His seconde wife waer Margaret Cusake by whom he had dasentine, Gerald, Robarte, George; Olenor, Anne and ta¬ terin.

Robte Pipho of Holywood deceased the ryt. of Aprill 1610. His firste wife was gemist dr. of¬ Ienco Lo: Vicounte of Gormanstowne (widow of Hen- vie sonne and heire of Sr. fo: Trabers Knight) by whom ipho, that had to wife M. pipho had issue, Trabers Elenor dr. of Tho: filmee of the Lions, all whose issue died. pouny; Fraunces wife to Dabid, sonne and heire to Geraldeetton of Castleton Kildraughte; and Cicilie wife to Bartholmew sonne and here of Tho: Ailmee of the Lions. No: pipio had to his seconde wife kin- borough Valentine, by whome he lefte issue Ruth
John wisson pentioner deceased the xxxth of Aprill 1610. he was never married, but leste issue James and Elizabeth bastardes
walter feilde of Dublin merchant deceased the thirde of May 1610: hio descent, match and Kijsue appeare in the visitation booke of Dublin begonne in ano. 1607. see Delafeild Vis.nt Entr Vol 2 p 51
Symon Bran^gan deceased the xvjth. of July 1610. he had to wife Margaret younge by: whome he had issue Amre now wise to Ja: Beé sometime Shireve of Dublin.
Christofer Cosgrave ato Nounea, sonne of Thomas Sometime alderman Maior of Dub: deceased the xxij. of Iuly 1610: he had to wife Garnewall. & had ijne onsy a dr.
James Jänes of Dublin alderman maior de- ceased the yyvn. of July 1610: his matchee and inue appeare in ij̈ vistation booke of Dublin for y yeere 1610. 1607.
John eldeste sonne of Edwarde fitz-geralde of Blackhall age about xvjen. yeares was des drouned the vijth of Auguste 1610. de Votre

Mabell dr. of Antony Broune vice-counte of Montacute, and ha: dowager of Geralde Erle of Kildare. deceased the xxv th of Auguste 2620. Shee had ihre Lo: Beralde y died before hio father, Henry Erle of whome in the for- mer funerall boote. Wiliam E. after hun dronned ijsules in Aprill 2599. ⁠ 2. drs Mary wi: to Chr. Lo: Ga: of Delvni. & Eliza- beth to Donogh E. of Thomond. Her funeral was cesébrated at ειταγηθη γχῆῃς. Septeƒ Shee id bur: at kildare.
Nicolas wycombe of „sasneeven deceased the xvijre. lo sept. 1610. His match e descente ap¬ peare in the visitacon booke of the countie of D Dublin for the yeere.
John Brice of Dublin aßderman major decea: sed the vixth of Septemb: 1610. his match & i sire appeare in the visitacon of Dublin a. 1607.

Mary La: dowager of Sir Christofer Augent kinghte Lo: Baron of Delbin, deceased the firste of Octob: 1610. Shee lefte issue Richard Lo: Baron of Helbin, = Christofer, Geralde, Thomas Gilberte and William; alsoe Mabell wife to Lo: Baron of Incebquin. Elizabeth Mmanin, to Geralde E. of Kildare Elenor to Christofer Chiber of Maceston, Mary to Ony elders sonne of Sir Terence o Demesie tinght, I Margaret and Julian.
Hath: Laundie wife of George Grimesdick deceased the xiiij. of october 1610. and leste Wisice by him Joan.
